. (A) fruiting branch, (B) inflorescence and flower buds, (C) upper view of fruit with remnants of the irregular calyx lobes, (D) cross section of fruit showing two locules and abnormally developed seeds. A, C, D from the holotype, B from the isotype. Scale bars for B and D = 1 cm, scale bar for C = 2 mm.
